omplished only with major reforms on the scale of the New Deal and the post-World War II building of new global institutions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 0aCapitalismzUnited States. 0aGlobalizationxEconomic aspects. 70(DE-601)1062737280(DE-588)4029577-1aKapitalismus2gnd 70(DE-601)3022971110(DE-588)4557997-0aGlobalisierung2gnd 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economic History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2018z978311066767708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520959071423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520959071.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066767-7  UC Press eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles